problem:
According to the table below, how many dollars are in the median value of the 59 salaries paid to this company's employees?

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|}
\hline
\textbf{Position Title}&\textbf{\# with Title}&\textbf{Salary}\\\hline
President&1&$\$130{,}000$\\\hline
Vice-President&5&$\$90{,}000$\\\hline
Director&10&$\$75{,}000$\\\hline
Associate Director&6&$\$50{,}000$\\\hline
Administrative Specialist&37&$\$23{,}000$\\\hline
\end{tabular}
solution: Since more than half the employees are Administrative Specialists, the median salary will be an administrative specialist, thus, $\boxed{\$23{,}000}$.
model_solution:
To find the median value of the 59 salaries, we need to arrange the salaries in order from lowest to highest. 

Since 37 of the employees are Administrative Specialists with a salary of $\$23{,}000$, the middle value will be the 30th salary (because 59 is an odd number, the middle value is the 30th value). 

The first 37 values are $\$23{,}000$, so we don't need to look at the salaries of the lower-paying titles. 

The next 10 values are $\$50{,}000$, and the 30th value would be the 7th $\$50{,}000$ (since we've already counted the first 37 salaries).

Therefore, the median value is $\$50{,}000$, which is the salary for an Associate Director.
